<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="12" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1558,1763]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1630,1655]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Distribution.</emphasis>
Previously reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[669,760,1631,1654]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko" box="[781,942,1630,1654]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" refString="Sirenko, B. I. (2001) Deep-sea chitons (Mollusca, Polyplacophora) from sunken wood off New Caledonia and Vanuatu. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire Naturelle, 185, 39 - 71." type="journal article" year="2001">
Sirenko 
<number box="[882,942,1630,1654]" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" value="2001.0">2001</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), the new records expand the distribution within 
<collectingCountry box="[230,322,1667,1690]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity box="[338,469,1666,1690]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.79" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="6.58" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="779.0" valueMax="900.0" valueMin="658.0">658–900 m</quantity>
) and also add records from the 
<collectingCountry box="[831,1019,1666,1690]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="11" pageNumber="12">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
(
<quantity box="[1036,1111,1666,1690]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.54" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="454.0">454 m</quantity>
, 
<quantity box="[1125,1270,1666,1690]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.765" metricValueMax="13.13" metricValueMin="6.4" pageId="11" pageNumber="12" unit="m" value="976.5" valueMax="1313.0" valueMin="640.0">640–1313 m</quantity>
). Found living and feeding on sunken terrestrial plant remains.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
